content.text:
- **Perseverance Rover Landing (Feb 18, 2021):** NASA’s Perseverance rover landed in Mars’s Jezero Crater to begin its mission of searching for signs of ancient microbial life and collecting rock samples for a possible future return to Earth ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perseverance_%28rover%29#:~:text=Cape%20Canaveral%20%20aboard%20an,evidence%20of%20past%20microbial%20life)).  
- **Ingenuity’s First Flight (Apr 19, 2021):** NASA’s Ingenuity helicopter became the first aircraft to achieve a powered, controlled flight on another planet (Mars), demonstrating that flight is feasible even in Mars’s thin atmosphere ([en.wikipedia.org](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ingenuity_%28helicopter%29#:~:text=Ingenuity%20made%20its%20first%20flight,terrestrial%20flight.%20%28It%20was)).
